<HEADLINE> Pakistan Stresses Importance of Missile Development </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ISLAMABAD, April 6 (Xinhua) -- Pakistan, as a sovereign state,
has the right to develop missiles which is of fundamental
relevance to its national security, a foreign office spokesman
said here Monday.
</P>
<P>
Addressing a crowded news conference, the spokesman confirmed
that Pakistan successfully carried out a test Monday on the
surface-to-surface Hatf-V (Ghauri) missile, which has a range of
1,500 kilometers and can carry a payload of 700 kilograms
"overland."
</P>
<P>
He said the test, using a missile developed with Pakistan's own
materials and technology, represented "a landmark" in the
country's missile and satellite launching program.
</P>
<P>
"Considering various developments in the region, especially
across the border, it is of fundamental importance to us," he said.
</P>
<P>
When asked if the missile test would intensify an arms race in
the region, the spokesman said, "We do not want an arms race, but
we cannot compromise on matters of national security."
</P>
<P>
He said Pakistan was willing to strengthen peace in the region,
but developments surrounding them had forced them to take measures
to safeguard the country's sovereignty and territorial integrity.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
