<HEADLINE> Ousted Afghan President Returns to Mazar-e-Sharif </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ISLAMABAD, April 6 (Xinhua) -- Ousted Afghan president
Burhanuddin Rabbani returned to the northern Afghan town of
Mazar-e-Sharif after a brief visit to Ashkabad.
</P>
<P>
During his stay in Ashkabad, Rabbani, leader of the
anti-Taliban Northern Alliance, met with U.N. special envoy
Lakhdar Brahimi.
</P>
<P>
The Afghan warring factions have agreed to hold talks in
Islamabad. The anti-Taliban Northern Alliance is expected to name
their delegation within ten days.
</P>
<P>
The Taliban militia has already announced the five members of
their delegation to the proposed talks in Islamabad. 
</P>
</TEXT>
