<HEADLINE> German Trade with Africa Up in 1997 </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BONN, April 6 (Xinhua) -- Germany saw its trade with Africa up
last year, with South Africa remaining its biggest trading partner
in Africa, said the German Economics Ministry Monday in a
statement.
</P>
<P>
German exports to Africa rose by 14 percent to 17.5 billion
marks (9.5 billion U.S. dollars) last year from 1996, while
imports from Africa were up 10 percent to 16.1 billion marks (8.7
billion dollars).
</P>
<P>
German exports to South Africa increased by 7 percent to 5.9
billion marks (3.2 billion dollars). Its imports from South Africa
totaled 3.6 billion marks (2.0 billion dollars), up nearly 16
percent. 
</P>
</TEXT>
