<DATE_TIME> 1998-04-06 18:32 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Netanyahu Welcomes Investigation Results Over </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JERUSALEM, April 6 (Xinhua) -- Israeli Prime Minister Benjamin
Netanyahu Monday expressed welcome to the conclusion of the
Palestinian investigation, which said Israel was not responsible
for Hamas activist Muhi Sharif's death.
</P>
<P>
Netanyahu received the report on the findings of the
investigation from Palestinian National Authority (PNA) President
Yasser Arafat, who briefed the prime minister's attorney Yitzhak
Molcho Monday afternoon.
</P>
<P>
The findings prove that this is an internal power struggle
inside Hamas (Islamic Resistance Movement), Netanyahu told
reporters here. He said that the PNA is apprehending the suspects.
</P>
<P>
Sharif, leading Hamas bomb maker, was found killed on March 29
in an industrial zone in the West Bank city of Ramallah.
Palestinian security officials said that Sharif was shot to death
before he was moved to his car, which was detonated later.
</P>
<P>
Netanyahu said that it confirmed Israel's previous statement
that it had no part in the affair, adding that "this is a positive
development."
</P>
<P>
He said that the findings show that "if PNA wants to, it can
fight terror."
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, Nabil Shaath, Palestinian minister of planning and
international cooperation, told a news conference in Ramallah that
the investigation has shown conclusively that Hamas members had
killed Sharif in a power struggle.
</P>
<P>
He said that the investigators had identified the murderer,
the weapon and his accomplices. Five Hamas members connected to
the murder have been arrested.
</P>
<P>
Other Palestinian officials said that the investigation had led
to the uncovering of large quantities of explosives, weapons and
time bombs in Ramallah.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, Palestinian Preventive Security Chief in the West
Bank Jibri Rajoub said that Palestinian security forces had
arrested some 30 Hamas activists in the last few days, who were
involved in Sharif's killing.
</P>
<P>
Israel accused Sharif of involving in several suicide bombing
attacks in Israel, including two explosions in Jerusalem last
summer, in which 25 Israelis were killed and about 200 others
wounded.
</P>
<P>
Although Israel has categorically denied any involvement in
the incident, Hamas has vowed to avenge Sharif's death,
declaring that they would attack Jewish targets both inside and
outside Israel. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
