<HEADLINE> Yeltsin Greets New Armenian President </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MOSCOW, April 6 (Xinhua) -- Russian President Boris Yeltsin
sent a congratulatory message Monday to Rubert Kocharian on his
election as Armenian president, according to the Interfax news
agency.
</P>
<P>
Yeltsin said he hopes that Kocharian will make contribution to
the development of mutual understanding and further strengthening
of the traditional friendship and cooperation between the two
countries and to regional peace and stability.
</P>
<P>
The Armenian Central Election Commission approved Monday the
final results of the presidential runoff held on March 30, when
Prime Minister Robert Kocharian collected 59.49 percent of the
votes, while his rival Karen Demirchian, the former Communist
Party chief, gained 40.51 percent, the report said.
</P>
<P>
The former Armenian president, Levon Ter-Petrosyan, announced
his resignation on February 3, forced by a political crisis in the
solution of the Nagorno-Karabakh problem. 
</P>
