<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Mozambique: CNE Condemns Intimidation </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MAPUTO, April 6 (Xinhua) -- Mozambican National Electoral
Commission (CNE) condemned Monday in a statement that some people
violated law by intimidation.
</P>
<P>
CNE said that these intimidating acts in the central provinces
of Sofala and Zambezia and the northern Nampula Province violated
the law and the freedom of the citizens.
</P>
<P>
"Intimidation can not be allowed in our multi-party democratic
process, and the intimidators shall be punished according to the
law," CNE warned.
</P>
<P>
CNE also noted that there were instigative and fraudulent
conducts of some political parties and individuals in the
signature-collection campaign.
</P>
<P>
According to reports from some voters, such conducts were
found in the cities of LIchinga in Niassa Province and Xai-Xai in
Gaza Province and the capital city of Maputo, CNE said.
</P>
<P>
It was reported that someone tried to bribe the voters with
soaps in order to run for Mayor.
</P>
<P>
The national electoral commission stressed that "Voters can
not be forced to support someone, no matter who he is."
</P>
<P>
CNE acknowledged that there were mistakes in the voters'
registration in mid-November and early December last year.
</P>
<P>
Some registers issued in 1994 were lost and there were
mistakes in the names of some voters, which will have impacts on
80,000 voters in 33 cities and towns.
</P>
<P>
CNE has decided that the mistakes would be corrected from
March 30 to April 13. But according to press reports, few voters
went to the designated sites to make correction.
</P>
<P>
The commission also announced Monday that election campaign
may go on from June 15 to June 27 for the elections scheduled on
June 30 in the 33 cities and towns.
</P>
<P>
Election results will be announced on July 15; from July 16 to
July 30, the elected members of the city councils will be
inaugurated; and the municipal presidents of the cities and towns
will be sworn in before August 4.
</P>
<P>
CNE said that the registration will come to an end on April 16
and the final list of candidates will be announced on May 31.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
