<HEADLINE> Ethiopia to Spend 230 Million U.S. Dollars on </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ADDIS ABABA, April 6 (Xinhua) -- The National Fertilizer
Industrial Agency of Ethiopia announced here Monday that it is
undertaking a project to ameliorate poverty and shortage of food
at a cost of over 230 million U.S. Dollars.
</P>
<P>
According to the Ethiopian News Agency, Zeleke Desalegn,
General Manager of the agency said that the fertilizer sector
project is deemed to boost agricultural productivity.
</P>
<P>
He said that the project is aimed at promoting the use of
fertilizers by farmers and creating enabling environment for the
production of natural and man-made fertilizers.
</P>
<P>
The International Development Agency and the Ethiopian
government have contributed 120 million U.S. Dollars and 110.4
million U.S. Dollars respectively for the execution of the
project, the general manager said.
</P>
<P>
According to him, the construction of eight soil test
laboratories will be carried out this year. 
</P>
</TEXT>
