<HEADLINE> Nigeria to Host African Summit on Drug Control </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LAGOS, April 6 (Xinhua) -- Nigeria will host the 10th African
summit of heads of drug law enforcement agencies scheduled for
April 20-24, the Nigerian Television Authority reported Monday.
</P>
<P>
The report said Nigerian Head of State, General Sani Abacha
will declare open the summit in capital Abuja, which is to
attract drug control experts from all over Africa.
</P>
<P>
The summit is jointly organized by the U.N. Drug Control
Program and the National Drug Law Enforcement Agency of Nigeria,
the report added. 
