<DATE_TIME> 1998-04-06 19:46 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> China Donates Relief Supplies to Iraq </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BAGHDAD, April 6 (Xinhua) -- A Chinese company on Monday
donated 10 tonnes of food and medicine to Iraqi children.
</P>
<P>
A chartered Ethiopian plane carrying the humanitarian goods
donated by Xi'an Microwave Communication Company in northwestern
China landed at the Saddam International Airport here at 17:50 GMT.
</P>
<P>
Iraqi Deputy Health Minister Khalid Jamil, who greeted a
nine-member delegation of the company, expressed Iraq's
appreciation for the initiative.
</P>
<P>
He said that the move of the Chinese company reflects the
strong and traditional friendship between the two countries and
the deep concern of the Chinese people for the Iraqi people who
have been under international sanctions for nearly eight years.
</P>
<P>
Ge Chuanxin, director general of the Xi'an Microwave
Communication Company, said that his company is intended to
express sympathy for the Iraqi people.
</P>
<P>
He called for the lifting of the economic sanctions as soon as
possible so that the Iraqis can rebuild their country.
</P>
<P>
The United Nations Security Council imposed sweeping embargo on
Iraq in 1990 after its invasion of Kuwait. The embargo has caused
serious shortage of food, medicine and other humanitarian goods in
the country. 
</P>
</TEXT>
