<DATE_TIME> 1998-04-07 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> EU Adopts New Cooperation Projects in R&AMP;D </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BRUSSELS, April 7 (Xinhua) -- The European Commission adopted
a program Tuesday for 204 new cooperation projects in research
and development with central and eastern European countries.
</P>
<P>
The program, with a total budget of 46 million ECU (49.2
million U.S. dollars), will focus on improving the environment of
these countries and the life of their people.
</P>
<P>
The program, proposed by Edith Cresson, European commissioner
in charge of research, education, training and youth, is part of
the European Union (EU)'s fourth Framework Program in Research and
Development.
</P>
<P>
The framework program aims at encouraging cooperation,
particularly in areas related to the improvement of living
conditions or public health, as well as the development of
industrial schemes in the energy, food and information society
sectors.
</P>
<P>
The European Commission, the executive body of EU, has received
nearly 1,300 proposals from research laboratories, businesses and
universities for cooperation projects costing 400 million ECU
(427.8 million dollars). 
</P>
</TEXT>
