<BODY>
<HEADLINE> China to Increase Certificate Bond Issue </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, April 7 (Xinhua) -- China will increase the issue of
its certificate treasury bonds by 17.36 billion yuan, the Ministry
of Finance announced today.
</P>
<P>
The five-year bonds, which will be on offer between tomorrow
and October 31, will carry an annual interest rate of 7.86
percent, according to the announcement.
</P>
<P>
Earlier this year the ministry announced the issue of 120
billion yuan in certificate bonds, which will be on offer through
October 31.
</P>
<P>
China issued a total of 241 billion yuan in treasury bonds last
year.
</P>
<P>
Statistics from the People's Bank of China, the central bank,
indicate that nearly 90 percent of the original issue has already
been sold.
</P>
<P>
As prices and interest rates on bank savings deposits keep
going down, more Chinese residents have turned to treasury bonds
as their main investment choice.
</P>
<P>
Since May 1996, China has cut bank interest rates four times,
with the latest on March 25.  
</P>
</TEXT>
