<HEADLINE> Primakov: Separation of Kosovo From Serbia "Unacceptable" </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MOSCOW, March 7 (Xinhua) -- Russian Foreign Minister Yevgeny
Primakov Tuesday described the attempt to separate Kosovo from
Yugoslavia as "totally unacceptable" after he met visiting Italian
Foreign Minister Lamberto Dini.
</P>
<P>
Such an attempt, which will not be accepted by Yugoslavia
either, will not promote negotiations between Belgrade and the
ethnic Albanians of Kosovo, it will only result in bloodshed,
Primakov told a press conference.
</P>
<P>
Primakov said he and Dini both agreed that the talks between
Belgrade and the Kosovo Albanians must start as soon as
possible. The Russian foreign minister pointed out that the talks
must be based on three principles including non-separation of
Kosovo from Yugoslavia.
</P>
<P>
The other two principles are granting Kosovo autonomy and
defining the relationship between Kosovo, with autonomy enjoyed
within the framework of Serbia and the federal central authority.
</P>
<P>
Primakov also stressed Russia's opposition against dispatching
troops to Kosovo.
</P>
<P>
Dini arrived in Moscow Monday for a three-day working visit.
</P>
<P>
The ethnic Albanians in Kosovo, who account for 90 percent of
the population of the province, have been seeking Kosovo's
independence from Yugoslavia. They came into armed conflict with
Serbian policemen in February. 
</P>
</TEXT>
