<HEADLINE> China Ranks First in Meat, Gourmet Powder Output in World </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHANGHAI, April 7 (Xinhua) -- Officials from the State Light
Industry Bureau declared here today that China ranks first in the
world in output of meat and gourmet powder.
</P>
<P>
Meat and gourmet powder output reached 59 million tons and
520,000 tons last year, respectively, officials announced at a
two-day workshop on China's food industry, which closed in
Shanghai today.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, the country's output value for the food-processing
industry has occupied first place, compared with all other
industries. So far, China has more than 60,000 enterprises engaged
in producing and processing food.
</P>
<P>
Liquor output topped 27 million tons in 1997, and the output of
beer was 18.6 million tons, second in the world.
</P>
<P>
Sources say that the rapid development of the food industry has
brought great changes in people's diets. Food sales in Shanghai's
900 supermarkets accounted for 73.8 percent of their sales in 1997.
</P>
<P>
Priority will be given to intensifying the processing of farm
products, and to produce more instant and healthy food, according
to officials.
</P>
<P>
Experts forecast that the country's food industrial output will
surpass 700 billion yuan by 2000, up 230 billion yuan over
1996. The annual average growth rate of the food industry is
expected to reach 11 percent.  
</P>
</TEXT>
