<HEADLINE> Global Chip Sales Rise in February </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NEW YORK, April 7 (Xinhua) -- World semiconductor sales hit
10.52 billion U.S. dollars in February, the second highest for the
month since 1990, the U.S. Semiconductor Industry Association
(SIA) reported Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
Sales in the American, European and Asia-Pacific markets
climbed 3.3, 7.7 and 6.6 percent from the figures in February 1997.
</P>
<P>
In Japan, the continued decline of the yen against the dollar
contributed to a sales reduction of 13.2 percent.
</P>
<P>
While overall stronger than 1997, world chip sales dipped 4
percent from January to February, the latest SIA statistics show.
</P>
