<TEXT>
<P>
WASHINGTON, April 7 (Xinhua) -- Nagano Olympic titlist Tara
Lipinski of the United States wants to be a professional figure
skater in order to spend less time training and more time with her
family, said a repors from Baltimore.
</P>
<P>
As a pro, Lipinski would be ineligible for amateur competitions
and would need to receive reinstatement as an amateur to skate in
the 2002 Olympics in Salt Lake City. Reinstatement by skating
authorities would not pose a problem.
</P>
<P>
The 15-year-old American spoke on a morning news-talk
television show from Baltimore, where she was to perform Wednesday
night in a figure skating show.
</P>
<P>
"I realized after Nagano how important it is to me to be with
my mom and dad and be all together and have fun and go out to
dinner and really be a family again," Lipinski said.
</P>
<P>
She said her training schedule in Detroit kept her from
spending much time with her family at home in Sugar Land,
Texas. She also said she'd like to go to college.
</P>
<P>
Lipinski has a new book coming out soon called "Totally Tara",
reports said. 
</P>
