<HEADLINE> China's Major Bank to Increase Business in Shanghai </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHANGHAI, April 7 (Xinhua) -- The China Construction Bank
(CCB), one of the country's four big state-owned commercial banks,
will this year increase lending to Shanghai and other large and
medium-sized cities and to key clients, bank president Zhou
Xiaochuan said today.
</P>
<P>
"CCB will grant more loans to large and medium-sized cities and
key clients, with particular attention paid to large cities such
as Shanghai," Zhou said here at a national work conference of the
Beijing-based bank.
</P>
<P>
CCB is confident about the economic growth prospects of
Shanghai and will expand its business in Shanghai, Zhou said.
</P>
<P>
"We should raise to a new level our credit investment in and
our overall services for Shanghai's key enterprises, important
construction projects and the reform of the residential housing
system," the president noted.
</P>
<P>
Bank figures indicate that CCB increased its loan portfolio in
Shanghai by 9.8 billion yuan last year and signed lending and
borrowing agreements with such large enterprises as Baoshan Iron
and Steel Group, Shanghai Petrochemicals and China Eastern
Airlines Group.
</P>
<P>
Over the recent years, CCB has invested a total of more than
eight billion yuan in power projects alone in Shanghai, in
addition to huge loans for construction of urban infrastructure
facilities such as major bridges, the subway system, and roads.
</P>
<P>
CCB has also been the first in Shanghai to grant mortgage loans
to individuals, totaling 100,000 by now.
</P>
<P>
Shanghai is China's leading economic and financial center.
