<HEADLINE> Corban Festival Celebrated in Beijing </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, April 7 (Xinhua) -- The China Islamic Association and
Beijing Friendship Association of Ethnic Groups held a reception
and a tea party today to celebrate the Corban Festival, one of the
most important Islamic holidays.
</P>
<P>
The Corban Festival falls on the 10th day of the last month of
the Hui Calendar, which is April 8 this year.
</P>
<P>
Among officials attending today's reception were Cheng Siyuan
and Tomur Dawamat, vice-chairmen of the Standing Committee of the
Ninth National People's Congress (NPC); Zhao Nanqi, vice-chairman
of the Ninth National Committee of the Chinese People's Political
Consultative Conference (CPPCC); Bai Lichen; Seypidin Azizi; State
Councillor Ismail Amat and other officials.
</P>
<P>
Also participating in the celebrations were diplomatic envoys
from Islamic countries as well as Muslim experts working in
Beijing.
</P>
<P>
China has 10 Islamic ethnic groups, including the Hui and Uygur.
</P>
<P>
The festival also was celebrated today in Ningxia, China's only
autonomous region of the Hui ethnic group, and Monday in northwest
China's Xinjiang Uygur Autonomous Region. 
