<HEADLINE> Pilgrims Perform Hajj Peacefully in Mecca </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KUWAIT CITY, April 7 (Xinhua) -- About 2 million pilgrims from
across the Muslim world performed Eid Al-Adha (feast of the
sacrifice) prayer peacefully Tuesday morning in the Grand Mosque
in Mecca, Saudi Arabia.
</P>
<P>
They walked around the Kaaba - the cubical structure in the
Grand Mosque in accordance with one of the main traditions of the
annual pilgrimage.
</P>
<P>
The prayer followed the climax of hajj - the rituals on Mount
Arafat on Monday.
</P>
<P>
In the prayer, the pilgrims shuffled shoulder-to-shoulder
inside the courtyard of the mosque loudly chanting "God is great",
amidst submissive fiducial atmosphere and joy, Kuwait News Agency
reports from Mecca said.
</P>
<P>
The hajj is one of the five pillars of Islam and every Muslim
should try to make the pilgrimage at least once in a lifetime.
</P>
<P>
Following the prayer this morning, the Mufti of the Grand
Mosques Sheikh Abdel Rahman Al-Sudais wished in his sermon that
all pilgrims would be able to perform all hajj rituals in peace
and harmony.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, Al-Sudais condemned Israel's "crimes in Palestine,
Aqsa Mosque and the holy city of Jerusalem," saying that the
"Zionists" have been trying "to spread their fabricated faith and
construct their alleged state on the holy Al-Aqsa Mosque."
</P>
<P>
He called on all Muslims to wage a holly war to liberating
these Islamic holy shrines from the hands of the Israel. 
</P>
</TEXT>
