<DATE_TIME> 1998-04-07 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Chinese Academy of Sciences to Invite More Visiting Scholars </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, April 7 (Xinhua) -- The Chinese Academy of Sciences
(CAS) will establish a system of senior visiting scholars this
year to make up for the aging of its research personnel and keep a
larger number of "transient" scientists.
</P>
<P>
The CAS will spend 24 million yuan (3 million U.S. dollars)
inviting 852 senior visiting scholars from at home and abroad
within the next three years, CAS Vice-President Bai Chunli told a
news conference today.
</P>
<P>
"Many core members of research groups at the CAS are getting old
and lack vitality, and most of its personnel are permanent
employees and cannot be replaced, which has hindered the progress
of the CAS," Bai said.
</P>
<P>
He said the new system is a breakthrough in CAS' management of
personnel resources. It will help the CAS become a more open
center of advanced scientific research and technology innovation
for both Chinese and foreign scientists, he said.
</P>
<P>
The visiting scholars should be those from outside the CAS who
have doctoral degrees and have been involved in scientific
research for more than five years, as well as foreign scholars and
overseas Chinese scientists who are professors or assistant
professors, according to the system.
</P>
<P>
All the scholars invited should be less than 45 years old, and
stay in the CAS for six to 12 months consecutively, according to
the system, and they can become employees of the CAS after that
period in a mutual decision between the scholars and the
institutes they have visited.
</P>
<P>
The first group of 853 senior visiting scholars will be
involved in the most advanced research projects, which include
nuclear technology, high-energy astrophysics, infrared remote
sensing, robot control and other projects in 88 institutes of the
CAS, Bai said.
</P>
<P>
He said that the CAS will strive to build itself into a national
knowledge innovation center within 10 years and provide abundant
resources for the country's technology innovation. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
