<HEADLINE> Tokyo Stocks Rise Sharply </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TOKYO, April 7 (Xinhua) -- Tokyo Stock prices shot up 1.74
percent Tuesday on both public fund support and late futures-led
buying.
</P>
<P>
The Nikkei Stock Average of 225 selected issues on the First
Section of the Tokyo Stock Exchange jumped 272.73 points from
Monday's close of 15,978.72.
</P>
<P>
The broader-based Tokyo Stock Price Index, covering all First
Section issues, advanced 11.08 points or 0.92 percent to 1,209.89.
</P>
<P>
Brokers said there was modest buying by public funds of
cyclicals and smaller-cap issues.
</P>
<P>
The key Nikkei index further gained in late trading, supported
by futures-led buying, brokers said.
</P>
<P>
"Very modest buying by public funds was seen among cyclicals,
aimed at preventing the Nikkei 225 index from falling below 15,500
points," a broker at Kokusai Securities said.
</P>
<P>
Volume on the First Section climbed to an estimated 400 million
shares from Monday's 380 million.
</P>
<P>
Nippon Steel was the day's volume leader.
</P>
<P>
Of the 1,328 listed issues, gainers outpaced losers 856 to 307,
with 117 remaining unchanged. 
</P>
</TEXT>
