<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Manila Allocates Rice to Address Food Shortage </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MANILA, April 7 (Xinhua) -- The Philippine National Food
Authority has stocked up its warehouses in Mindanao with some
200,000 bags of rice which will be made available anytime to food
shortage-stricken provinces and towns, the Philippine News Agency
reported Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
To alleviate the situation in Mindanao, Agriculture Secretary
Salvador Escudero has instructed all regional directors of the
Department of Agriculture to facilitate the distribution of rice
and render whatever food assistance to affected areas.
</P>
<P>
Escudero also instructed his men to come up with a master list
identifying the local government units and provinces which are
really affected by the lack of food.
</P>
<P>
President Ramos earlier directed all affected local government
units to spend a portion of their allotments to provide for the
necessary resources to allow flow of food supply in their
respective areas in this state of emergency.
</P>
<P>
Escudero said the situation in Mindanao in being closely looked
into and necessary measures to cushion the impact of food shortage
are being put in place in close coordination with the regional
disaster coordinating council. 
</P>
</TEXT>
