<HEADLINE> Sino-US Commercial Law Seminar to Feature Anti-Dumping Issues </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, April 7 (Xinhua) -- The ninth Sino-US Commercial Law
Seminar which focuses on commercial arbitration and anti-dumping
issues opened here today.
</P>
<P>
The two-day seminar was organized by the Chinese Ministry of
Foreign Trade and Economic Cooperation (MOFTEC).
</P>
<P>
Addressing the seminar, Sun Zhenyu, vice-minister of MOFTE said
that regular communications in the fields of commercial law would
benefit the bilateral commercial ties between the two countries.
</P>
<P>
Andrew Pincus, general counsel of the US Department of
Commerce co-hosted the seminar with Zhang Yuqing, acting director
general of MOFTEC's Law and Treaty Department.
</P>
<P>
Also attending the seminar were representatives from China's
Supreme People's Court, China Arbitration Committee for
International Trade, the U.S. Commerce Department, business people
and lawyers. 
