<HEADLINE> Ningxia Hui Autonomous Region Celebrates Islamic Festival </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
YINCHUAN, April 7 (Xinhua) -- Leading Party and government
officials of the Ningxia Hui Autonomous Region met here today with
360 Muslim representatives of the Hui and Uygur ethnic groups to
mark their traditional Corban Festival.
</P>
<P>
Han Maohua, deputy secretary of the Ningxia Regional Committee
of the Communist Party of China (CPC), extended festival greetings
to the ethnic groups in the region on behalf of the CPC regional
committee and the local government.
</P>
<P>
He said the 5.3 million Han and Hui people in the region are
living in harmony and that they have boosted prosperity and
advanced various causes of the autonomous region since its
establishment 40 years ago.
</P>
<P>
The region's gross domestic product reached 21 billion yuan
(2.5 billion U.S. dollars) in 1997, while its grain output was
2.567 million tons despite a drought, Han said.
</P>
<P>
Ningxia, China's only autonomous region of Hui ethnic group, was
founded in October 1958. There are 1.7 million Hui Muslims,
one-third of the region's total population.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
