<HEADLINE> China Issues White Paper on Science and Technology </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, April 7 (Xinhua) -- China today announced a list of
major state construction and research projects that welcome
overseas participation.
</P>
<P>
Xu Guanhua, Vice-Minister of Science and Technology, said today
that the projects include hi-tech pharmaceutical and
environmental protection industries, Beijing-Shanghai express
railway line and information highway.
</P>
<P>
He added that high-definition television, computer financial
network, electrically operated motor cars, Three Gorge project,
super-conductive technology and flood prevention system are also
on the list.
</P>
<P>
He said at a news conference for issuing "White Paper on
Science and Technology No. 7" that the Sino-overseas cooperation
will focus on research of key technology programs and introduction
of overseas funds and technology for China's construction and
development projects.
</P>
<P>
Xu said China also prepares to introduce quality crop seeds,
advanced agro-technology and equipment, invite overseas
specialists and introduce technology for upgrading large and
medium-sized state-owned enterprises.
</P>
<P>
The white paper, entitled "Guide to China's Science and
Technology Policy", announces that China welcomes establishment of
research institutions by overseas research bodies and setting up
Sino-overseas cooperative research entities.
</P>
<P>
The vice minister disclosed that France is preparing to
establish a life science institution in China's leading industrial
city of Shanghai as well as an information center and a
sustainable development center in the Chinese capital.
</P>
<P>
He added the US Bell company also plans to build a lab in
Shanghai.
</P>
<P>
The white paper tells of China's scientific and technological
development plans for its Ninth Five-Year Plan period (1996 to
2000) and long-term development objectives to the year 2010, apart
from implementing the relevant plans and policies. 
</P>
</TEXT>
