<DATE_TIME> 1998-04-07 13:12 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Arab States to Strike Anti-Terrorism Accord </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CAIRO, April 7 (Xinhua) -- Arab ministers of interior and
justice will initial a draft agreement on fighting terrorism and
radicalism here on April 22, the Middle East News Agency reported
Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
The accord will serve as the foundation of effective Arab
cooperation in security and safety, Egyptian Minister of Justice
Farouk Seif el-Nasr told reporters Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
He said it will denounce all forms of violence and terrorism
and bases its clauses on the principles of Islam and international
law, the U.N. Charter and all international pacts on the fighting
of terrorism on land, sea and air.
</P>
<P>
Once the agreement is endorsed, it will play a key role in
helping Arab security bodies fight and constrict the phenomenon of
terrorism in the Arab world, said a security source of the
Egyptian Ministry of Interior.
</P>
<P>
Egypt has been fighting a violent campaign launched by Islamic
militants since 1992 aimed at overthrowing President Hosni
Mubarak's secular government and installing strict Islamic rule.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
