<HEADLINE> Bomb Blast Kills Five, Injures 27 in Pakistan </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ISLAMABAD, April 7 (Xinhua) -- Five passengers were killed and
27 others injured in a powerful bomb blast Tuesday morning in
central Sindh province of Pakistan.
</P>
<P>
According to a report by the Associated Press of Pakistan, the
bomb exploded Tuesday morning on a passenger bus coming from
Hyderabad in the southern part of Sindh to the central Sindh city
of Nawabshah.
</P>
<P>
The accident happened when the bus stopped at a local petroleum
station for fuel.
</P>
<P>
The bomb is reported to have been kept under a front seat. The
blast was so powerful that it tore apart the bus from the middle,
said the report.
</P>
<P>
Three passengers were killed on the spot while two others
succumbed to their injuries after being rushed to a nearby
hospital. Among the injured, seven are in serious condition.
</P>
<P>
Emergency was declared in the hospital and all the doctors were
called to duty. Volunteers gathered in large numbers to donate
blood, according to the report.
</P>
<P>
The report quoted an official of the Bomb Disposal Squad in
Nawabshah as saying that it was a time-device with some 250 grams
of explosive.
</P>
<P>
This was the second bomb blast Tuesday morning in Sindh
province. A 45-year-old woman was killed and another 10 people
injured when a bomb exploded at a bus stand in Khairpur city of
Sukkur District.
</P>
<P>
The bomb is reported to have been planted in a hollow tree near
the bus stand, and it exploded during the rush hour. 
</P>
</TEXT>
