<HEADLINE> Albania Sees Lower Infant Mortality </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TIRANA, April 7 (Xinhua) - With improved medical conditions and
more education on hygiene, Albania has seen a drop in the infant
mortality rate in the past several years.
</P>
<P>
The mortality rate in 1997 was down nearly 1.3 percent from
that of 1992, Health Ministry officials said Monday.
</P>
<P>
Infant mortality in 1997 declined to 22.5 per 1,000 from 35 per
1,000 five years ago, official statistics claim. Nevertheless, the
rate still tops the list of all European countries, and it is
three times that of developed countries.
</P>
<P>
Therefore, much work remains ahead for Albania to lower its
infant mortality rate, officials stressed. 
</P>
