<HEADLINE> Woodforde Slaps Philippoussis </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CANBERRA, April 7 (Xinhua) -- Australia's shock Davis Cup
defeat by Zimbabwe has caused a split in the team with Mark
Woodforde slaps Mark Philippoussis for refusing to play and then
turning up as a spectator.
</P>
<P>
Woodforde said relations between Philippoussis and the rest of
the team would take a long time to heal.
</P>
<P>
Woodforde, a Davis Cup veteran but primarily a doubles
specialist, was forced to play in the reverse singles against
Zimbabwe after world number four Pat Rafter dropped out because of
illness.
</P>
<P>
Philippoussis had refused to play in the tie because of a
public feud with team captain John Newcombe. But Philippoussis
arrived as a spectator for the tie at late notice, and apparently
uninvited, to cheer on the team.  
</P>
</TEXT>
