<HEADLINE> Foreign Investment in Romania Amounts to 2.8 Billion Dollars </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BUCHAREST, April 7 (Xinhua) -- Foreign investment in Romania
has totalled 2.8 billion U.S. dollars over the last eight years,
the Romanian Agency for Development (ARD) reported Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
1992 was a peak year for capital inflow when foreign investment
amounted to 812 million dollars and some 12,300 foreign-Romanian
joint ventures were set up.
</P>
<P>
The ARD data also shows that between December 1990 and February
1998 joint ventures in Romania numbered 54,532.
</P>
<P>
G-24 countries are the main source of foreign investment,
accounting for 74 percent of the total, followed by countries from
the European Union with 54 percent. 
