<DATE_TIME> 1998-04-07 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> U.S.-Back ACRI Won't Replace ECOMOG: Ghanaian </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LAGOS, April 7 (Xinhua) -- The African Crisis Response
Initiative (ACRI) sponsored by the U.S. will not help enhance
peacekeeping operation in west African in stead of replacing the
sub-regional force ECOMOG, said a Ghanaian officer.
</P>
<P>
Clayton Yaache of the ghanaian army said here at the weekend
that the U.S. initiative was a means to an end and not an end
itself.
</P>
<P>
Yaache is the leader of a group of students of the Ghana
Command and Staff College now on a visit in Nigeria.
</P>
<P>
Ghana, along with other African countries such as Senegal,
Uganda, Malawi,Mali and Ethiopia, has endorsed the training of
its troops by the U.S. under the ACRI.
</P>
<P>
According to Yaache, the training of an African crisis
response force does not in any way affect the existence of
ECOMOG, the Post Express quoted the Ghanaian officer as reporting
Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
Instead, Yaache said, it would enhance the capacity of
countries within ECOMOG to effectively keep peace.
</P>
<P>
ECOMOG would continue as a peacekeeping force after its
successful installation of democracy in Liberia and Sierra Leone,
he said, suggesting "We will be on standby and ensure the peace.
But if for any reason there is another operation, ECOMOG will
continue".
</P>
<P>
Yaache, who headed a 20-man delegation from Ghana comprising
12 students and eight directing officers, said, "If ACRI would
enhance future peacekeepng in the sub-region, so be it. But i
cannot see it completely replacing ECOMOG because there are other
countries that make up ECOMOG."
</P>
<P>
Currently, researchers at Nigeria's National War College are
studying the U.S.-sponsored initiative, aimed to find out the
real facts behind it.
</P>
<P>
It seems that Nigeria is in the view that what African
countries need in terms of peace keeping is logistics support
since many of them have been involved in one peacekeeping mission
or the other in many parts of thet world for some time.
</P>
<P>
A senior leader of the college said earlier that at the end of
the study, also being conducted in conjunction with some
organizations in Africa, real facts behind the initiative would
be revealed with a view to highlighting its implications on
Africa.
</P>
<P>
Nigeria has expressed its hope that an all-African
peacekeeping force could be built with ECOMOG as the nuclues.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
