<TEXT>
<P>
MOSCOW, April 7 (Xinhua) -- Russia's State Duma (the Lower
House of Parliament) decided Tuesday to discuss President Boris
Yeltsin's appointment of Sergei Kiriyenko as prime minister on
Friday, the Interfax news agency reported.
</P>
<P>
Yeltsin will address some 20 representatives of leading
parliamentary groups at a roundtable meeting later Tuesday, and
the debate will not be held until the Duma has discussed the
outcome of the meeting in the next two days, the Duma's Acting
Speaker Vladimir Ryzhkov said.
</P>
<P>
