the Duma's plenary session, he said. "The situation remains quite
complicated so far, but serious consultations are under way," he
added.
</P>
<P>
President Yeltsin fired his entire government two weeks ago and
nominated 35-year-old Kiriyenko as the candidate for premier,
threatening to disband parliament if it fails to endorse him.
