<DATE_TIME> 1998-04-07 08:46 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> 4 Israelis Killed, 39 Wounded in S. Lebanon </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIRUT, April 7 (Xinhua) -- Four Israeli soldiers have been
killed and 39 others wounded in south Lebanon in the first three
months of this year during clashes with Lebanese guerrillas, the
Daily Star newspaper reported Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
Quoting statistics released by Hezbollah, the Iranian-backed
Islamic resistance force, the paper reported that eight militiamen
of the pro-Israeli South Lebanon Army (SLA) were also killed.
</P>
<P>
On the guerrilla side, 16 anti-Israeli-occupation fighters lost
their lives during the clashes.
</P>
<P>
According to the statistics, Israeli assaults on Lebanon,
including air raids, shelling and roadside bombings, totaled 112
in March, while Lebanese guerrillas conducted 114 operations
against Israeli and SLA troops in the Israeli occupied south
Lebanon.
</P>
<P>
Hezbollah, or Party of God, which is spearheading a war against
Israeli troops and its ally SLA in south Lebanon, carried out 105
attacks in March alone, down from February's figure of 117, the
highest number in one month since 1985.
</P>
<P>
Israel set up a 1,200-square-kilometer "security zone" in south
Lebanon in 1985 after two invasions, with the claimed aim of
protecting its northern part from cross-border guerrilla
attacks. It has since been bogged down in an attrition war with
resistance forces there.
</P>
<P>
Israel offered to pull out of Lebanon provided security
arrangements are worked out with Lebanese government. Beirut,
however, has rejected the offer, saying the U.N. Security Council
resolution 425 calls for unconditional and immediate Israeli
withdrawal. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
