<HEADLINE> Tanzania, Kenya to Cooperate in Combating </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
DAR ES SALAAM, April 7 (Xinhua) -- Tanzania and Kenya have
vowed to cooperate in fighting drug trafficking and other crimes
in their border areas, local newspaper The Guardian said Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
A meeting held Monday and attended by senior government
officials from Tanzania and Kenya, decided the the two countries
will exchange intelligence information and work out strategies to
crack down on cross-border crimes which are on the increase in
recent years.
</P>
<P>
On robbery and theft of motor vehicles and motor cycles, the
directors of Criminal Investigations from both countries agreed
to organize frequent operations to curb the menace.
</P>
<P>
The Kenyan authorities have also promised to assist Tanzania
in seizing lawbreakers involved in the theft of electrical and
telephone cables in Tanga Region and in the recovery of the
stolen wires.
</P>
<P>
The meeting held in Tanga Region in east Tanzania also
commended the existing brotherly cooperation between the two
neighboring countries. 
