<HEADLINE> Rapid Increase in Machinery, electric products Exports in Liaoning </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHENYANG, April 7 (Xinhua) -- Northeast China's Liaoning
Province exported more than two billion US dollars worth of
machinery and electric products last year for the first time.
</P>
<P>
The 2.37 billion US dollars worth of goods were a 25.3 percent
increase from the previous year. They have become the province's
single largest export item, accounting for 31.5 percent of its
total exports last year.
</P>
<P>
In addition to its traditional markets of Hong Kong, Southeast
Asia, Japan, North America, and Russia, Liaoning now also exports
its machinery and electric products to the Middle East, Africa and
Latin America.
</P>
<P>
Machinery, telecommunications equipment, appliances, and
automobiles and auto components made up 74.6 percent of Liaoning's
exports of machinery and electric products last year.  
