technology for producing radio and television programs while tens
of thousands of representatives from major electronic companies
are trying to sell cameras, transmitters, monitors and other
equipment needed in the transformation of the broadcasting system.
</P>
<P>
At the Las Vegas Convention Center, where the four-day show is
held, visitors marveled at digital TV sets receiving digital
pictures provided by Las Vegas KLAS Channel 8, the world first
digital broadcasting station.
</P>
<P>
Developing digital technology has been on the NAB's agenda for
years. Stations in New York, Los Angeles, Chicago, Las Vegas,
Dallas and other five largest cities will start broadcasting
digital signal before the deadline of May 1999. All other stations
will begin digital broadcasting no later than May 2002.
</P>
<P>
Earlier this year, major manufacturers in the world, including
Panasonic, Sharp, Sony, Matsushita, Zenith and Philips,
demonstrated their digital TV sets during the 98' Winter Consumer
Electronics Show also held in Las Vegas. These companies will sell
their products in U.S. markets soon. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
