<HEADLINE> Eastern Chinese City Developing Commercial Streets </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NANJING, April 7 (Xinhua) -- Nanjing, capital of Jiangsu
province in east China, will build five special commercial streets
with 430,000 square meters of business space in the next few
years, selling food, name-brand products, fashionable goods,
high-tech products, and hardware.
</P>
<P>
Nanjing had total retail sales of 34.5 billion yuan last
year. Some of its commercial streets are known nationally, like
1.8-kilometer-long Pearl River Street, which has 11,000 square
meters of business space, and annual sales of computers and parts
of more than two billion yuan. There are plans for increasing that
space to 80,000 square meters.
</P>
<P>
Food street, in the "Confucian Temple" area in southern part of
Nanjing, is another traditional commercial center, and
1.6-kilometer-long Taiping Street will increase its business space
from 50,000 square meters to 150,000 square meters.
</P>
<P>
One-kilometer-long Hunan street, with its fashionable items,
will expand its business space from 50,000 square meters to
100,000 square meters.  
</P>
