<HEADLINE> Water Conservation Stressed in Southern China </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
GUANGZHOU, April 7 (Xinhua) -- The capital of south China's
Guangdong Province has put 2.6 billion yuan into water
conservation in the past three years, almost twice the amount for
the years from 1949 to 1994.
</P>
<P>
A city government official says that water conservation has
been raised to the level of resources and communications in its
policies.
</P>
<P>
Since 1995, the government has developed a three-year plan for
water conservation, building 270 key projects, improving 839
kilometers of dykes, and adding 38.86 million cubic meters of
earth and stone.
</P>
<P>
From 1991 to 1996, it put 200 million yuan into six flood
protection projects.
</P>
<P>
The Guangzhou government also did work on the Pearl River area,
spending 270 million yuan since 1995. 
</P>
