<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Sino-Belarus Extradition Treaty </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, April 7 (Xinhua) -- The People's Republic of China and
the Republic of Belarus today ratified a treaty on extradition.
</P>
<P>
China's Vice-foreign Minister Zhang Deguang and Belarus's
ambassador to China, Vyachaslau Kuznyatsou, attended the signing
ceremony of the treaty, which takes effect on May 7.
</P>
<P>
The treaty covers conditions, procedures, and expenses for
extradition and says that the two countries are responsible for
extraditing persons from the other country who face criminal
charges in the one country's territory.
</P>
<P>
This is the second treaty signed by the two countries, after
the Treaty on Judicial Assistance in Civil and Criminal Matters,
which took effect in 1993. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
