<HEADLINE> Technology Growth in Northwestern Chinese Province </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LANZHOU, April 7 (Xinhua) -- Northwest China's Gansu province
has been placing great importance on technology and in 1996, the
province evaluated 3,500 technology contracts worth 264 million
yuan.
</P>
<P>
The province ranks ninth in terms of technology strength among
China's provinces, municipalities and autonomous regions and is
one of the country's science and technology research centers.
</P>
<P>
In recent years, it has set up a management network of
technology markets, developing technology business and information
exchanges, and sponsoring science and technology exhibitions at
trade fairs.
</P>
<P>
The province now has over 1,200 science and technology
agencies, employing 4,000 people, and science and technology
institutes have become active in this.
</P>
<P>
Private businesses are getting involved in transferring
technology and in consultation service and account for a third of
the technology trade in Gansu. 
