<HEADLINE> Shanghai's Monthly Stock Trading Up 50 Percent </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHANGHAI, April 7 (Xinhua) -- Stock prices on the Shanghai
Exchange continued to rise in March, according to official
statistics, with the benchmark Composite Stock Index closing at
1,243 points, up three percentage points from the previous month.
</P>
<P>
Stock turnover for March was up 50 percent from February to
more than 91.2 billion yuan.
</P>
<P>
The most significant increase was in public utilities,
high-technology products, construction, energy, and in companies
that are restructuring assets.
</P>
<P>
