<DOCNO> XIE19980407.0206 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1998-04-07 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> U.S. Bans Import of Assault Firearms </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WASHINGTON, April 6 (Xinhua) -- U.S. President Bill Clinton
Monday ordered to ban the import of 1.6 million rifles on the
ground that the weapons were military-style ones unnecessary for
the Americans to use them for hunting and sporting.
</P>
<P>
"These are military weapons, weapons of war," said Clinton, who
made the order to bar 58 high-powered, foreign-made guns with
large-capacity magazines after a finding that they failed to meet
an exemption to U.S. gun laws as a sporting rifle.
</P>
<P>
Most of the affected guns were variations of the AK-47 and Uzi
semiautomatic weapons.
</P>
<P>
"They were never meant for a day in the country and they are
certainly not meant for a night on the streets," Clinton said at
the White House in announcing the decision.
</P>
<P>
Press secretary Mike McCurry said the announcement was made
"within the context of a nation that is still grieving" from the
recent schoolyard shootings in Jonesboro, Arkensas, that left
five killed and 11 wounded.
</P>
<P>
However, the weapons that the school-boys used would not be
covered because they were made in the United States, not imported.
</P>
<P>
Clinton said foreign gun makers were making "minor cosmetic
modifications" to skirt the law. To those manufacturers, he said,
"You can read the fine print in our law and our regulations all
you want and you can keep making your minor changes. But we're
going to do our best to keep our people alive and stop you from
making a dollar the wrong way."
</P>
<P>
The decision to ban the weapons makes permanent a temporary ban
that the administration imposed last November on assault weapons.
The order follows a Treasury Department review of 59 weapons.
</P>
<P>
Firearms importers had permits to ship in nearly 600,000
altered guns, and applications were pending for 1 million more.
The administration's action prevents the sale of those weapons.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE19980407.0207 </DOCNO>
