<HEADLINE> Vietnam Airlines Carries Fewer Passengers in First Quarter </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HANOI, April 7 (xinhua) -- The Vietnam Airlines experienced a
sharp drop in the number of passengers in the first quarter of
this year, only one fourth that of the same period of last year.
</P>
<P>
As reported by Vietnam's English daily Vietnam News Tuesday, by
the end of March 31, it had carried some 620,000 passengers on its
domestic and international flights, far fewer than it did in the
corresponding period of last year -- 2,593,000.
</P>
<P>
Vietnam Airlines has proposed to cut passenger services on
those unprofitable routes.
</P>
<P>
In the same period, it carried 10,840 tonnes of cargo,
representing 24 percent of its annual target for 1998. 
