<HEADLINE> Sri Lanka Attracts Russian Tourists </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
COLOMBO, April 7 (Xinhua) -- The Sri Lankan Tourist Department
is pushing hard to expand its share of the Russian tourist market,
the local newspaper reported Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
Under the auspices of the Ceylon Tourist Board, 12 Sri Lankan
tour operators and hotels participated in Moscow International
Travel and Tourist Fair this year.
</P>
<P>
It was reported that 3,618 Russian tourists visited Sri Lanka
last year, an increase of 21 percent over the previous year.
</P>
<P>
Although this is only about one percent of the total tourist
arrivals in the country, Russian tourists spend an average of 55
U.S. dollars per person per day, which are three times higher than
the average spending of all tourists in Sri Lanka.
</P>
<P>
Apart from the beaches and rich culture which attract the
Russian tourists, the traditional friendship established between
the two countries during the period of the cold war, is considered
as a major attraction, Colombo hotels sources said
</P>
<P>
A permanent resident representative is reportedly to be
appointed soon for the Russian tourist market and a Russian team
is expected to visit Sri Lanka to promote Russian films in the
country.
</P>
<P>
The sources believed that the true potential of Russian tourist
to Sri Lanka is ten fold of the present tourists figure. 
</P>
