<HEADLINE> Poland to Limit Coal Imports </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WARSAW, April 6 (Xinhua) -- Poland plans to restrict the amount
of coal imports in a bid to protect its own coal industry.
</P>
<P>
The Polish newspaper Law and Economy reported Monday that
initially, the country's general customs administration will
impose quality checks on imported coal following Economic Ministry
guidelines.
</P>
<P>
Poland, the fourth largest coal producer in the world, has seen
a slump in production in recent years due to rising costs and has
turned to imported coal.
</P>
<P>
Last year, the country's coal industry lost more than 500
million U.S. dollars.
</P>
<P>
To help revitalize the industry, the Polish government this
year plans to shut down a number of loss-making coal mines and lay
off 30,000 miners. 
</P>
