<DATE_TIME> 1998-04-07 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Study Calls For Higher Agriculture Investment </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, April 7 (Xinhua) -- Latest research shows a
significant shortfall and a year-on-year decline in China's
investment in agricultural science and technology, according to
today's China Daily.
</P>
<P>
This fall-off has resulted in a brain drain and decreasing
scientific yields, said the survey, conducted by the Agricultural
Economics Institute under the Chinese Academy of Agricultural
Sciences.
</P>
<P>
Since 1985, funds allocated to agricultural scientific research
have had a slight increase in some years and decreased in others,
according to the survey.
</P>
<P>
On average, State financial investment fell by 0.8 percent a
year during the 1985-95 period.
</P>
<P>
However, when added to input from the scientific organizations
themselves, investment totalled 5.2 billion yuan (626 million
U.S. dollars) in 1996, compared with 1.4 billion yuan in 1985.
</P>
<P>
In overall terms, investment more than tripled. However,
average annual growth was just 2.5 percent in real terms, the
survey reported.
</P>
<P>
Even in 1996, when the Agriculture Law and the Law on
Scientific Advancement were both in effect, the increase in funds
allocated to agricultural science and technology lagged far behind
the growth in investment in other fields.
</P>
<P>
"The results were worse than we expected", said Ma Shiqing,
director of the Science, Technology and Quality standards
Department of the Ministry of Agriculture.
</P>
<P>
He also noted that the poor situation demonstrated by the
findings is likedly to lead to new measures and greater fundings
by the ministry and other sources.
</P>
<P>
The survey concluded that the government should increase
investment in agricultural science and technology by eight percent
annually. This would allow the achievement of the ambitious goal
of making China self-sufficient in food by 2030 when the
population is expected to reach 1.6 billion.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE19980407.0234 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1998-04-07 </DATE_TIME>
