<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Argentina Issues Bonds in ECUs </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BUENOS AIRES, April 6 (Xinhua) -- Argentina is to issue 750
million ECUs (808 million U.S. dollars) of bonds.
</P>
<P>
This is the first time for Argentina to issue bonds in the
European monetary market as well as the largest and longest term
issuance of a Latin American country.
</P>
<P>
The bonds, to be issued on April 21 for a ten-year term, will
be placed at a price of 98.84 percent of their nominal value and
will produce an 8.3 percent profit for the investors. 
</P>
</TEXT>
