</P>
<P>
-- Some 400 students, farmers and small businessmen took to the
streets Monday in the southern Philippine city of Cotabato to
demand rice from the government amid widespread drought in the
region that threatens to leave one million people hungry.
</P>
<P>
Manila Bulletin:
</P>
<P>
-- The Energy Regulatory Board Monday ordered oil firms to cut
the prices of three "socially sensitive" fuel products by an
average of 40 centavos (1 U.S. cent) per liter effective 6 a.m.
Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
The Manila Times:
</P>
<P>
-- A Philippine anti-graft court Monday virtually confirmed the
Marcos family's secret move to split 75-25, in government's favor,
the Marcoses' 540 million U.S. dollars Swiss funds. 
