<HEADLINE> Brief Economical News From Latin-America (1) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MEXICO CITY, April 6, (Xinhua) -- The following are brief economic
news from Latin-America in the recent week.
</P>
<P>
BUENOS AIRES -- Automobile industries of Argentina and Brazil
have signed an agreement on the industry's policy to be adopted in
the South American Common Market (Mercosur) in year 2000.
</P>
<P>
A report of the Argentine Association of Assembly Plants said
the manufacturers have agreed on the main points which would form
the future system of the automobile industry in the trade bloc.
</P>
<P>
SAN JOSE -- The Costa Rican Ministry of Treasury in the first
quarter of the year has closed 118 business firms for evasion of
the federal income tax, company tax or consumption tax.
</P>
<P>
Since 1995, when the new act of tax was enacted, the government
has closed 538 businesses.
</P>
<P>
BRASILIA -- Sugar production in Brazil will reach 1.4 million
tons in the 1997-1998 season and alcohol production will rise to
600 million liters, according to Jorge Toledo, president of the
Brazilian Sugar and Alcohol Industry Trade Union.
</P>
</TEXT>
