<BODY>
<HEADLINE> United States Beat Russia 3-2 </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WASHINGTON, April 6 (Xinhua) -- United States beat Russia 3-2
in a Davis Cup tennis tie after Jim Courier grabbed a decisive
rubber over Russian Marat Safin in Stone Mountain, Georgia, on
Sunday.
</P>
<P>
Courier squeaked out a 0-6, 6-4, 4-6, 6-1, 6-4 victory in a
reverse singles for the overall victory in a World Group
first-round tie.
</P>
<P>
He dropped to his knees on the court after clinching the last
point with a spectacular service winner in a nearly three-hour
game.
</P>
<P>
Earlier in the day, American Andre Agassi lost a 6-3, 6-0, 7-6
(7-3) reverse singles fourth round rubber against Yevgeny
Kafelnikov to make the fifth rubber a live match.
</P>
<P>
The Russian went into game strongly by winning the first eight
games of the match.
</P>
<P>
But the more experienced Courier then changed tactic to start
slicing his backhand to take some of the steam from Safin.
</P>
<P>
Although Safin was able to capture the third set, Courier was
in control of the final two sets. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
