<HEADLINE> Chongqing Development Zone Welcomes Overseas Investment </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, April 7 (Xinhua) -- With the improvement of its
infrastructure, the economic and technological development zone in
Chongqing, China's fourth municipality, is welcoming overseas
investment.
</P>
<P>
The zone has played a leading role in developing the economy
in the western regions of China, said Tang Wenfeng, director of
the zone's administrative office.
</P>
<P>
He said the zone, which was established seven years ago, had
attracted more than 250 overseas-funded enterprises by the
end of 1997, with a combined overseas investment of 1.1 billion
U.S. dollars.
</P>
<P>
So far, the zone has generated 4.7 billion yuan in industrial
output value and 170 million U.S. dollars in imports and exports.
</P>
<P>
Tang said the zone, the only national economic and
technological development zone in western China, will be a golden
area for foreign investment in the fields of automobile,
motorcycle, information, food processing, medicine, and chemical
industries. 
</P>
</TEXT>
