<DATE_TIME> 1998-04-07 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> China Enhances Harbin-Dalian Railway Electrification </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHENYANG, April 7 (Xinhua) -- China this year will invest 2.31
billion yuan in the electrification of the Harbin-Dalian Railway,
a major rail line in northeast China.
</P>
<P>
The amount is four times as much as the sum for the
electrification project in the last four years.
</P>
<P>
Harbin is capital of northeast China's Heilongjiang Province
while Dalian is a major city on the southern tip of coastal
Liaoning Province. The railway also runs through Jilin Province.
</P>
<P>
This year the electrification project will focus on
construction of railway facilities in Harbin, Changchun, capital
of Jilin Province, Shenyang, capital of Liaoning Province, and
Dalian.
</P>
<P>
Telecommunications and power transmission lines along the
946.5-kilometer railway line between Harbin and Dalian will be
completed by the end of this year.
</P>
<P>
The entire electrification project is scheduled for completion
in 2000.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
