<DOCNO> XIE19980407.0262 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1998-04-07 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> NZ Review of Police Expected to Boost Efficiency </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WELLINGTON, April 7 (Xinhua) -- New Zealand Police Commissioner
 Peter Doone has indicated that a review of the police will
increase the frontline capability.
</P>
<P>
Doone was quoted by a TVNZ report Tuesday as saying that "I am
confident that the review will result in a more efficient police
service and boost our frontline capability."
</P>
<P>
He said the aim of the review is to ensure that police
management is as lean and cheap as it can be. The police can
learn lessons from the way private companies are managed.
</P>
<P>
His comment came after Police Minister Jack Elder announced on
Monday a review to investigate whether some services and jobs can
be cut or contracted out to help save money for frontline
policing.
</P>
<P>
The review will focus on management and administration to save
spending on the police. It followed criticism of the cost of a new
 computer system for the police and a pay dispute between the
government and police officers.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE19980407.0263 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1998-04-07 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Two Major Financial Services Announce Big Merge </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NEW YORK, April 6 (Xinhua) -- The New York-based Citicorp and
Travelers Group are merging in a record 82 billion U.S. dollar
deal combining the second-biggest bank with a leading provider of
financial services in the U.S..
</P>
<P>
Today's announcement sent both companies' stock prices soaring.
</P>
<P>
The deal easily surpasses the previous record price of 37
billion U.S. dollars that the telecommunications company WorldCom
is paying for MCI.
</P>
<P>
The new company would be called Citigroup Inc., would use
Travelers' trademark red umbrella as its logo, and would have more
than 100 million customers in 100 countries.
</P>
<P>
It would have assets of almost 700 billion U.S. dollars,
revenue of nearly 50 billion U.S. dollars and operating income of
approximately 7.5 billion U.S. dollars.
</P>
<P>
Citicorp is the parent company of Citibank, the international
banking powerhouse, and also is the world's largest issuer of
credit cards with some 60 million bank cards.
</P>
<P>
Travelers Group is an insurance, brokerage and investment
banking giant. Its operating companies include Salomon Smith
Barney, Travelers Life &AMP; Annuity, Travelers Property Casualty
Corp., Primerica Financial Services, and Commercial Credit.
</P>
<P>
The merger will mean that the two companies' customers will
have easier access to a much broader range of financial services.
For example: Citicorp account holders can now transfer money by
telephone or personal computer between checking, savings and money
market accounts. And they will also be able to make transfers
between those accounts, plus Travelers' insurance and mutual fund
products.
</P>
<P>
Large financial companies have said for a long time that
studies have shown their customers want this type of one-stop
shopping.
</P>
<P>
Analysts said that it remains to be seen how the on-line
revolution will affect people's way of getting financial services.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
