<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Burundi to Receive New UNDP Support </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
UNITED NATIONS, April 6 (Xinhua) -- The United Nations
Development Program (UNDP) and the Government of Burundi have
launched a 6 million U.S. dollar reconstruction and rehabilitation
program to help the country recover from civil conflict, according
to UNDP.
</P>
<P>
Along with funding efforts to improve agriculture, public
administration and the environment, the program will support
income-generating activities for families and communities, the
UNDP said here on Monday.
</P>
<P>
The civil conflict brought ruin to much of the African
country's agriculture. Some 700,000 Burundians are still living as
refugees or are internally displaced because of the conflict which
began in 1993. 
</P>
</TEXT>
