<HEADLINE> 4 Percent German Output Rise Expected in 1998 </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BONN, April 6 (Xinhua) -- German industrial output would grow
by at least four percent this year, almost the same level as in
1997, the Munich-based economic research institute Ifo predicted
Monday.
</P>
<P>
Ifo said the main growth of production would occur in
electrical and plant engineering and in automobiles, as a result
of a weak mark, moderate wages and an industry-wide reduction of
200,000 jobs.
</P>
<P>
In 1997, German output increased by 4.2 percent thanks to very
strong exports.  
